             <string>&lt;html&gt;&lt;head/&gt;&lt;body&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color:#ffff7f;&quot;&gt;Select the calculation mode based on which capacitor is given.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color:#ffff7f;&quot;&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color:#ffff7f;&quot;&gt;• Full Analysis: use C1 and/or C2 together to find the overall low cutoff range.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color:#ffff7f;&quot;&gt;• C1 only: use only the input coupling capacitor C1.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color:#ffff7f;&quot;&gt;• C2 only: use only the output coupling capacitor C2..&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color:#ffff7f;&quot;&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color:#ffff7f;&quot;&gt;For quiz questions that say “due to C1/C2 only,” choose the matching mode.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;</string>
